I see the term thrown around “entrepreneur” “business owner” “coach” from a lot of folks out there on the magical internet…. I can tell you this. Running a business is much more than putting up videos talking of “coaching” “business knowledge” with some cool quotes or echoed knowledge from a book they read… It’s not that easy and those aren’t businesses… Running employees, customer service, manufacturing, Human Resources, logistics, understanding back end operations and accounting. Lawyers, sales staff, COGS, marketing, inventory, account relationships, designers, packaging, product development, shipping, amazon maintenance, finance, e-commerce, multiple store fronts, on and on. That is a business… Sleeping on the floor of your store when in time of desperation. Having huge years of sales crushing it, then loosing it all. Rebuilding from scratch… This is business ownership. So be cautious with all of these “successful business people” or coaches who you pay that have never run a true business… At least ask them to show you what they’ve built before paying anyone anything for advice… This ain’t easy and I call BS when I see it pushed all over the place. To those who know and run a true business, you know this truth well. If you are dreaming of building a true scaleable business or are doing so now. I commend you as I know the sacrifice and work it takes. Keep at it and avoid the “I have the secret guy” I put my stamp on that… CEO and Founder Rogue American and Invader Coffee ~ Wes Whitlock

social_posts.post_text: When I was a kid, there were certain places I was forbidden. Places that were what I thought, unattainable or foreign. Places that had gates and locks around the doors of my mind.  Coming from schools starting with elementary- until 8th grade where I eventually was thrown out (self imposed). That system programmed me to believe I was “mentally too slow” I fell behind and was embarrassed to even go into a classroom fearing the teachers would further stab into my young dreams.  A University was another planet to me and a place that would be forsaken in my young mind.  Now years later, being invited to University’s as a guest to speak to Veteran Business MBA students and professors is almost surreal to me as it feels nature now.  To any young person or anyone out there on a journey where you feel out of place or “different” it’s a great gift so embrace it and let no one kill it.  I look back now to that kid who struggled so much, thank you for never giving up on us. This is your one life, there are no doors un breach-able.  Keep that fire inside burning strong.

Got to interview @wes_whitlock on behalf of the Student Veterans Association and Business School at St. Edward’s University. 

I’ve seen a lot of bullshit in the veteran community about “veterans helping veterans”, but Wes is the real deal. 
He gave a down and dirty about his experience as a prior Marine in the entrepreneurial space and didn’t hold any punches. It was the honest look we all needed, and he offered some solid advice, mainly to be genuine to your brand and hold to your mission & morals. 

I’ve been to countless events like this and he’s the only guest speaker I’ve seen stay until the lights turned off, making sure he answered every single person’s question. Seriously cool. 

Check out his company @rogueamericanshop, his seriously good air-roasted coffee at @invadercoffee, and his podcast “Going Rogue with Wes Whitlock”.

I’ve been reading a great book I’d like to share as it’s become a great source of useful knowledge on self. We are surrounded more than ever by external distractions that are mentally devastating to many, especially our youth and even adults (possibly more so in some cases). We are in abundance out loud microphones and huge egos with loud voices telling you how great they are and that you too can be like them if you listen to them…. From our schools, to our culture, the fear controlling media and anywhere you look…. What is not being mentioned is the importance of internal awareness and growth. This is something never taught to us in Western Civilization. We are taught only to Be the best, compete, be better than everyone one, etc… Driven by loud platforms.  Something I too battle with especially in an aggressive business climate, looking to balance such things while working on inner peace where the truth dwells.  Being louder in the fist and quieter in the mouth you can learn a great deal. Each person is a unique and special yet programmed to want to be something other than self and that is where turmoil grows like a weed. Everything important in this short life is not found in a treasure on top of a mountain. It’s all inside but that can be even harder to find so we search outside where they tell us to go… The book is called The Search by OSHO explains the 10 bulls (Self). I’ve put a few passages on my stores and a lot have asked what this book is. So wanted to pass along in the case it may help guid someone back inside themselves as it’s helped me find some truth and peace. This ride is short so manage where you give your mind and time. Keep less lighting in your mouth and more thunder in your your fist. #truth #innerguidance #innervoice #innerpeace

Ive spent my life in the life of service to my Country and our way of life. As a young man I believed that everything. I bounced around this world from the best to the worst places imaginable in the service to others and in protecting that as an oath or badge of honor of purpose. As I get I get older, I have begun to think deeper than that once sought purpose of adventure and creed. I now enjoy building my own life and that for the sake of my children and those close to me who I love. I work to build a better future for my loved ones and self as I’ve learned we must fulfill our dreams or we will commit a death inside that will be unforgiving if not maintained. With so much to distract us or pull us from ourselves in almost a guilty manner, we must maintain our dreams of building the best life we can and with that we can do and be more of those we love. Along that path you will have lost some who were close, but you will maintain the ones meant and you will find others who share your aspersions and fuel you as you them. Veterans Day late post.  I never felt I belonged and always wanted an adventure in life especially after reading lonesome dove as a teenager. Seeing full metal jacket and reading Semper Fi comic books I saw my escape and lighthouse. After struggling with school my entire young life labeled a special Ed kid, I knew the system was wrong and started working out and turning my grades around so that I could graduate and join, it gave me the purpose and drive I was looking for. No girlfriends or parties, I started working out and worked to save money as I felt there was something greater for me. Told I couldn’t pass a physical due to a bad skateboard accident on my back. I found a way through weights and fixed my back. I found that family in the Marines and will forever be grateful. Both for the love and hate I had for it, it gave me the confidence and greatest gift of adventure and brotherhood I wanted. Not for everyone, but it was what I needed to find my potential and fill my passions. I don’t dwell in laurels but I never forget where I came from. To any young person who struggled as I did, I’d never push the Military on them but for the one who feels this. I know you and your passion can’t be stopped by the school system or anyone telling you can’t. Find your way #semperfi #usmc #adventure #veteransday
